"Self-Describing Object Architecture"
for 
UHA Inventory Management System

Moduler
Self-declaration — every object announces its own identity, dependencies, and capabilities via MANIFEST
Self-documentation — every object carries its own narrative, issues, and changelog via DOCS
Self-registration — the system discovers and wires from declarations, nothing is hardcoded externally

roadmap~

repo/
├── app.py                          ← pure shell, never changes
├── base.py                         ← contract (Dashboard, StubMixin, validators)
├── registry.py                     ← auto-discovery + dispatch
├── docs_generator.py               ← run to regenerate all docs
├── database.py                     ← existing (unchanged)
├── auth.py                         ← existing (unchanged)
├── modules/
│   ├── dashboard_module.py         ← ✅ reference implementation
│   ├── dashboard_module_doc.py     ← ✅ companion diagnostic
│   ├── import_dashboard.py         ← next
│   ├── import_dashboard_doc.py     ← next
│   └── ...
└── docs/                           ← generated, never hand-edited
    ├── SYSTEM_MANIFEST.md
    ├── DEMO_CHECKLIST.md
    └── dashboard_module.md
The workflow for every new module:

Copy dashboard_module.py → rename → fill in MANIFEST, DOCS, render()
Copy dashboard_module_doc.py → update the two constants at the top (__module__, import line)
Run python modules/new_module_doc.py --validate — must be all green before anything else
Run python docs_generator.py — docs write themselves
Drop in modules/ — registry picks it up automatically on next app start

common diagnostic commands:

bashpython modules/dashboard_module_doc.py           # full spec sheet
python modules/dashboard_module_doc.py --validate  # CI-style pass/fail
python docs_generator.py --demo-check           # demo readiness report



